translated: Lindgren, Carl Olof, lawyer, Tenhult, b. 22/2/08 on Visingsö, Jönköping. 1st child of gamekeeper, Carl L., and Emma Strömberg. Married in 1937 to Vera Adelsköld. Children: Marianne b. 1939, Göran b. 1941, Håkan and Karin b. 1943. Completed high school in Jönköping in 1927, graduated with a law degree from Uppsala University in 1933. Served as a clerk in Vartofta and Frökind court districts from 1933 to 1936, assistant and temporary secretary for water rights at Västerbygd water court from 1936 to 1938, employed at Axel Falmström's law firm in Jönköping from 1938, became a partner in 1942. Member of the Swedish Bar Association since 1940.
